-- Omega Founder Robinson in Talks With FMG, Telegraph Reports
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2012-04-07T12:58:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-07/omega-founder-robinson-in-talks-with-fmg-telegraph-reports.html
John Robinson, the founder of  Omega
Insurance Holdings Ltd. (OIH) , a Lloyd’s of London underwriter, has
held advanced discussions with Fund Management Group, the Daily
Telegraph reported, without saying how it obtained the
information.  FMG hopes wants to build a 15 percent stake in the company
and overhaul its executive team including Chief Executive
Officer Richard Pexton, the newspaper said. Omega declined to
comment while Robinson couldn’t be reached for comment, the
Telegraph said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnieszka Troszkiewicz in London at 
 atroszkiewic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
